Definition
A pseudo-class is used to define a special state of an element.

Example:
:hover
:nth-child()

:hover and :nth-child()
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
 <meta charset="UTF-8" />
 <title>Pseudo Class Example</title>

 <style>
   p {
     border: 2px solid maroon;
     height: 200px;
     width: 200px;
     text-align: center;
     background-color: black;
     color: whitesmoke;
     font-size: 20px;
   }

   /* Hover effect */
   p:hover {
     background-color: yellow;
     color: maroon;
   }

   /* Select third child */
   p:nth-child(3) {
     background-color: goldenrod;
     color: black;
   }

   /* First child hover */
   p:nth-child(1):hover {
     background-color: green;
   }

 </style>
</head>

<body>
 <p>First box</p>
 <p>Second box</p>
 <p>Third box</p>
 <p>Fourth box</p>
 <p>Fifth box</p>
</body>
</html>

